## 8. Information-Theoretic Interpretation

Information possesses independent existence. Patterns may shift media or lose organization, but the underlying asset density is rarely absolute zero.

The theorem is compatible with — and may be a special case of — **information ontology**: the view that reality is fundamentally structured information rather than matter alone.

### Salvage-First Engineering (Applied Corollary)

Waste is not zero. A broken machine, an outdated database, a toxic chemical byproduct — these are unallocated, high-entropy assets. True production is never *ex nihilo* (from nothing); it is the mechanical extraction and reorganization of high-entropy noise back into low-entropy utility.

*"Waste is not zero"* is the engineering translation of *"nothing does not exist."*

