## 9. Collective and Layered Reality

Reality possesses multiple coexisting layers, each with its own maintenance requirements and decay modes:

| Layer | Description | Maintenance Agent |
|---|---|---|
| **Personal Reality** | Private experience, memory, identity | The individual |
| **Shared Reality** | Consensus among groups; social facts | Collective agreement and enforcement |
| **Physical Reality** | Observable external phenomena | Thermodynamic processes (partially self-maintaining) |
| **Symbolic Reality** | Laws, money, nations, languages, institutions | Collective belief and institutional infrastructure |

Symbolic realities are among the most powerful and fragile. They exist only because minds collectively sustain them. They can achieve E > 1 (nations, currencies, religions) but collapse catastrophically when the sustaining collective disbands.

